opennlp.ccg.hylo.graph
Class LFVertex

java.lang.Object
  opennlp.ccg.hylo.graph.LFVertex

public class LFVertex
extends Object

A vertex in an LFGraph. Vertices are based on SatOps, encapsulating their nominal and proposition argument (or null if there is no associated proposition). Vertices also maintain a list of attribute/value pairs representing their associated attribute/value predications.

The index and type of an LF vertex are determined by the specified nominal's name. For example, if a vertex's name is w12, then getIndex() returns 12 and getType() returns LFVertexType.WORD.

Author:
Scott Martin
See Also:
LFGraph, LFVertexType, SatOp

getAttributeMap

public Map<Mode,Proposition> getAttributeMap()
Gets the attribute map associated with this LF vertex. Note that the returned map is not modifiable; to modify a vertex's attributes, the methods setAttribute(Mode, Proposition) and removeAttribute(Mode) should be used.

Returns:
An unmodifiable copy of the attribute map encapsulated by this vertex, or Collections.EMPTY_MAP if no attributes are present.

toString

public String toString()
Gets a string representation of this LF vertex. For example, if this vertex's name is w9, its proposition's name is walk, and its attribute map contains num=sg and det=nil, this method returns w9@walk {num=sg, det=nil}.
